text: Yeah, so the first print you’re trying to make is tricky because the parts you want to cut out aren’t connected to each other. The laser is just going to cut along a line, and you have a bunch of concentric circles that aren’t connected. You can either cut them out as a bunch of separate pieces and just position them how you want when you spray paint, or you need to modify your design so that the pieces are actually connected. This could be by adding thin connectors between the circles. Basically, just remember that the laser cuts along a line, so if you want one piece, you need to give it one continuous line to cut along.

text: For your second cut, the lines you want to cut out are just single lines- so the laser will cut one line the width of the laser. If you want to spray paint through it, you want to cut out an actual hole, so you need to define a width. You can do this by using rectangles instead of lines, so that the laser will leave a hole behind.
